      "content": "The concept you are looking for is the \"tyranny of the majority,\" famously articulated by James Madison in *The Federalist Papers*, which warns that even well-meaning majorities can abuse their power to oppress minorities if left unchecked by constitutional limits. This aligns with the \"slippery slope\" argument, which posits that granting the government broad regulatory powers over the internet inevitably corrupts those institutions, regardless of their initial noble intentions, because power itself is inherently corrupting. Therefore, the only way to prevent this inevitable drift toward tyranny is to strictly limit government authority over digital spaces, ensuring that the internet remains a free zone where no single entity, even a benevolent one, can dictate the flow of information.",
